[{"location":"api/#Fcp.jl-API-Reference","page":"API","title":"Fcp.jl API Reference","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/","page":"API","title":"API","text":"This section contains the API reference for the Fcp.jl package, detailing the available functions and their usage.","category":"page"},{"location":"api/#Module-Overview","page":"API","title":"Module Overview","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/","page":"API","title":"API","text":"Fcp.jl consists of several modules:","category":"page"},{"location":"api/","page":"API","title":"API","text":"Fcp: The main module that contains the primary main() function for executing the copy operations.\nCLI: Handles command-line argument parsing.\nCore: Contains the core logic for running the file copying operations.\nConfig: Deals with loading and managing configuration settings.\nUtils: Provides utility functions used throughout the library.","category":"page"},{"location":"api/#Main-Function","page":"API","title":"Main Function","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/#Fcp.main()","page":"API","title":"Fcp.main()","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/","page":"API","title":"API","text":"Description: The entry point for running Fcp from the command line.\nArguments: None (relies on command-line arguments for configuration).\nUsage:\nFcp.main()","category":"page"},{"location":"api/#Config-Module","page":"API","title":"Config Module","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/#Config.load_settings(config_path::Union{String,-Nothing})","page":"API","title":"Config.load_settings(config_path::Union{String, Nothing})","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/","page":"API","title":"API","text":"Description: Loads the configuration settings from a file, if provided.\nArguments:\nconfig_path: Path to the configuration file.\nReturns: A Settings object containing the configuration.","category":"page"},{"location":"api/#Core-Module","page":"API","title":"Core Module","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/#Core.run(args::Dict{String,-Any},-settings::Config.Settings)","page":"API","title":"Core.run(args::Dict{String, Any}, settings::Config.Settings)","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/","page":"API","title":"API","text":"Description: Runs the main copying operations based on provided arguments and settings.\nArguments:\nargs: A dictionary containing command-line arguments.\nsettings: The settings object containing configuration options.","category":"page"},{"location":"api/#Core.parallel_copy(files::Vector{Path},-dest::Path,-pattern::String,-logger)","page":"API","title":"Core.parallel_copy(files::Vector{Path}, dest::Path, pattern::String, logger)","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/","page":"API","title":"API","text":"Description: Copies files in parallel to the destination.\nArguments:\nfiles: A vector of file paths to be copied.\ndest: Destination directory path.\npattern: Pattern to filter files.\nlogger: Logger instance for verbose output.","category":"page"},{"location":"api/#CLI-Module","page":"API","title":"CLI Module","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/#CLI.parse_arguments()","page":"API","title":"CLI.parse_arguments()","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/","page":"API","title":"API","text":"Description: Parses command-line arguments.\nReturns: A dictionary of arguments parsed from the command line.","category":"page"},{"location":"api/","page":"API","title":"API","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"api/","page":"API","title":"API","text":"For further questions or contributions, please check out the repository.","category":"page"},{"location":"usage/#Usage-Guide-for-Fcp.jl","page":"Usage","title":"Usage Guide for Fcp.jl","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"usage/","page":"Usage","title":"Usage","text":"This section provides a guide on how to use the Fcp.jl package for various file copying scenarios.","category":"page"},{"location":"usage/#Basic-Command-Line-Usage","page":"Usage","title":"Basic Command-Line Usage","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"usage/","page":"Usage","title":"Usage","text":"To use Fcp from the command line, simply call the main function with appropriate options:","category":"page"},{"location":"usage/","page":"Usage","title":"Usage","text":"Fcp [options] source destination","category":"page"},{"location":"usage/#Options","page":"Usage","title":"Options","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"usage/","page":"Usage","title":"Usage","text":"-r, --recursive: Copy directories recursively.\n-v, --verbose: Enable verbose output to track the copying progress.\n-p PATTERN, --pattern PATTERN: Only copy files that match the specified pattern (e.g., *.txt).\n-c CONFIG, --config CONFIG: Path to a configuration file for additional settings.","category":"page"},{"location":"usage/#Examples","page":"Usage","title":"Examples","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"usage/","page":"Usage","title":"Usage","text":"Basic Copy\nFcp source_directory destination_directory\nRecursive Copy\nFcp -r source_directory destination_directory\nCopy Files Matching a Pattern\nFcp -p \"*.txt\" source_directory destination_directory","category":"page"},{"location":"usage/#Using-a-Configuration-File","page":"Usage","title":"Using a Configuration File","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"usage/","page":"Usage","title":"Usage","text":"You can use a configuration file to set default options for your copy commands. The configuration file should be in TOML format and can specify default patterns, verbosity, etc.","category":"page"},{"location":"index copy/#Fcp.jl","page":"Fcp.jl","title":"Fcp.jl","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"index copy/","page":"Fcp.jl","title":"Fcp.jl","text":"Welcome to the documentation for Fcp.jl.","category":"page"},{"location":"index copy/#Introduction","page":"Fcp.jl","title":"Introduction","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"index copy/","page":"Fcp.jl","title":"Fcp.jl","text":"Fcp.jl is an advanced file copying utility written in Julia.","category":"page"},{"location":"index copy/#Installation","page":"Fcp.jl","title":"Installation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"index copy/","page":"Fcp.jl","title":"Fcp.jl","text":"Instructions on how to install and use Fcp.jl.","category":"page"},{"location":"index copy/#Usage","page":"Fcp.jl","title":"Usage","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"index copy/","page":"Fcp.jl","title":"Fcp.jl","text":"Examples and usage instructions.","category":"page"},{"location":"index copy/#API-Reference","page":"Fcp.jl","title":"API Reference","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"index copy/","page":"Fcp.jl","title":"Fcp.jl","text":"```@autodocs Modules = [Fcp]","category":"page"},{"location":"#Fcp.jl-Documentation","page":"Home","title":"Fcp.jl Documentation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Welcome to the documentation for Fcp.jl, a Julia package that provides advanced file copying capabilities with features such as parallel copying, configurable patterns, and more.","category":"page"},{"location":"#Overview","page":"Home","title":"Overview","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Fcp.jl is designed to facilitate efficient copying of files and directories, offering additional features like recursive copying, filtering by patterns, and verbose output. Whether you're dealing with a large number of files or specific file types, Fcp.jl aims to simplify and speed up the process.","category":"page"},{"location":"#Features","page":"Home","title":"Features","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Parallel Copying: Utilize multiple threads to copy files concurrently, reducing the time required for large copying tasks.\nPattern Matching: Specify file patterns to include or exclude during the copying process.\nRecursive Directory Copying: Easily copy entire directory structures with an optional recursive flag.\nConfigurable Settings: Use a configuration file to manage copying settings.","category":"page"},{"location":"#Installation","page":"Home","title":"Installation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"To install Fcp.jl, add it to your Julia environment using the following command:","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"using Pkg\nPkg.add(url=\"https://github.com/Luftalian/fcp\")","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"After installation, you need to compile the project to use it as a command-line tool. First, clone the repository:","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"git clone https://github.com/Luftalian/fcp.git","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Navigate to the cloned directory:","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"cd fcp","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Use the following command to compile the application:","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"julia --project -e 'using PackageCompiler; create_app(\".\", \"fcp\"; precompile_execution_file=\"precompile_script.jl\")'","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"After compiling, set the PATH to use the compiled application:","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"export PATH=\"fcp/bin:$PATH\"","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"You can now use Fcp as a command-line tool:","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Fcp -h","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"For detailed usage and API information, check out the Usage and API sections.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"For further questions or contributions, please check out the repository.","category":"page"}]
